{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"precious-spy-hellbender","description":"# Wire store-wide overlap step into review_plan (LLM-gated, graceful skip, advisory surfacing)\n\n## Why\nThe overlap check must fire in the tolerant window before claim — during `review_plan` — and fold its results into the plan-review output as advisory coaching, without ever blocking the claim. This is the integration seam that ties Cupid enrichment + retrieval + judge into the agent workflow.\n\n## What\n- In `review_plan` (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:352`), after the existing passes, run the store-wide overlap step: synchronously extract the query ticket's digest from the already-assembled full-text context (S1), run stage-1 retrieval (S5), run stage-2 judge (S6), and attach the ≤3 advisory findings (each with its `rebar link` command) to the verdict's advisory/coaching section.\n- LLM-gate: if the `[agents]` extra, plan-review, or API key is absent, the step GRACEFULLY SKIPS (no findings, no error, claim proceeds).\n- Config flag to enable/disable the overlap step independently.\n- Surface through the CLI (`rebar review-plan`) and MCP (`review_plan`) outputs.\n\n## Scope\n- IN scope: the orchestration/wiring, advisory surfacing with suggested commands, graceful-skip gating, config flag, CLI+MCP surface. OUT: the component ops (S1/S5/S6), the async corpus enrichment (S2/S3/S4).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `review_plan` on a ticket runs the overlap step and includes ≤3 advisory overlap findings (with `rebar link` commands) in its verdict — and the claim is NEVER blocked by them.\n- [ ] The query digest is generated at review time from the ticket's current full text (not dependent on the ticket being in the enriched corpus).\n- [ ] When the `[agents]` extra / plan-review / API key is absent, the step is a silent no-op and review_plan behaves exactly as before.\n- [ ] A config flag independently enables/disables the overlap step.\n- [ ] Findings appear in both the CLI `review-plan` output and the MCP `review_plan` result.","id":"0f70-6d61-2b78-4c34","parent_id":"bd83-c56f-1f72-4ef2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Wire store-wide overlap step into review_plan (LLM-gated, graceful skip, advisory surfacing)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783568209521652001,"uuid":"07f3e1b5-4a0c-4781-8876-c08826b60307"}